    "summary": "Current activities (2013-present): \n- Industrial consultancy for ILO-Net (sponsored by NWO)\n- Dutch Member of FIIF Management board, preparing the way for future operational use of nuclear fusion at a European level\n\nPrevious activities at Dutch Space (1982-2013):\n1998 - 2013:\tBusiness Development Manager for instruments-related programmes, e.g.:\n\u2022\tEarth Observation Space instruments: GMES-Sentinel 4/5, TropOMI, OMI, SCIAMACHY, BIOMASS\n\u2022\tAstrophysics Space instruments: Darwin, GAIA, SPICA/SAFARI, IXO\n\u2022\tSpace exploration & life science instruments: SPEX, Life Marker Chip, bio-analysis instrumentation for Space and ground-based applications\n\u2022\tDownstream data processing, e-collaboration and Grid computing infrastructure\n\u2022\tGround-based astrophysics instruments: LOFAR, ELT, VLT\n\u2022\tLarge Science infrastructures: ITER, CERN\n\u2022\tR&D programmes for Climate research, forest monitoring, SAR applications, cryogenic coolers\n\n1993 \u2013 1998:\tManager of product group Remote Sensing & Small Systems with particular orientation to business development. Areas of interest were microgravity, small satellites, instrumentation, infrastructure and applications for optical and radar Space-based remote sensing, airborne remote sensing and strategic collaboration with companies, technological institutes and universities in these areas.\n\n1988 \u2013 1993:\tGroup manager in the departments Attitude Control and Thermal Control consecutively. Tasks included Human Resources Management and coaching related to the attitude control projects ISO and SAX and development of new business areas, such as payloads for Earth Observation.\n\n1982 - 1988:\tVarious study and project activities, particularly in a coordinating role, e.g. IRAS mission analysis and flight operations, ISO and SAX AOCS phase A/B/C/D",
